# include ‚Äî Project Header Files

This directory holds global header files shared across `src/` and all `lib/` modules.

---

## Pinout.h

**File**: `include/Pinout.h`

Single source of truth for all GPIO pin numbers and I2C addresses. Every library module and `main.cpp` includes this file; hardware assignments are never hardcoded elsewhere.

### I2C Bus

| Define | Value | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| `I2C_SDA` | 21 | Shared SDA line for both multiplexers |
| `I2C_SCL` | 22 | Shared SCL line for both multiplexers |
| `MUX_ADDR_SENSORS` | 0x70 | TCA9548A #1 ‚Äî environmental sensors (A0,A1,A2 ‚Üí GND) |
| `MUX_ADDR_MICROFLUIDICS` | 0x71 | TCA9548A #2 ‚Äî pumps and flow sensors (A0 ‚Üí 5V, A1,A2 ‚Üí GND) |

### Control Board (direct ESP32 pins)

| Define | GPIO | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `PIN_TEMP_PCB` | 36 (VP) | Analog input for PCB NTC thermistor (B57164K103J) |
| `PIN_ITO_CONTROL` | 32 | PWM output shared by both ITO glass heaters |
| `PIN_PWM_FANS` | 12 | PWM output for PCB cooling fan |

> **ITO glass heaters**: two panes (top rectangular 7‚Äì10 Œ©/sq, bottom square 15‚Äì20 Œ©/sq) are wired in parallel to `PIN_ITO_CONTROL` and driven by a single signal ‚Äî no independent per-glass control.
>
> **Incubator circulation fan**: a separate DC fan powered directly from the bench power supply (not the ESP32) runs inside the incubator chamber at all times. It is not connected to any ESP32 pin.

### UV LED Array

| Define | GPIO | LEDC channel | Group |
|--------|------|-------------|-------|
| `PIN_C1_LEDS` | 18 | 0 | LED group 1 |
| `PIN_C2_LEDS` | 19 | 1 | LED group 2 |
| `PIN_C3_LEDS` | 25 | 2 | LED group 3 |
| `PIN_C4_LEDS` | 26 | 3 | LED group 4 |

### Sensors Board (via MUX 0x70)

| Define | MUX channel | Device |
|--------|-------------|--------|
| `MUX_CH_TEMP1` | 2 | SHT35 #1 ‚Äî top sensor |
| `MUX_CH_TEMP2` | 3 | SHT35 #2 ‚Äî bottom sensor |
| `MUX_CH_UV` | 4 | LTR390 UV sensor |

CO‚ÇÇ sensor (T6615) uses dedicated UART2: `PIN_CO2_RX` = GPIO 16, `PIN_CO2_TX` = GPIO 17, 9600 baud.

### Microfluidics Board (via MUX 0x71)

| Define | MUX channel | Device |
|--------|-------------|--------|
| `MUX_CH_PUMP_1` | 2 | mp-Lowdriver ‚Äî Pump 1 (fluid, circuit 1) |
| `MUX_CH_PUMP_2` | 3 | mp-Lowdriver ‚Äî Pump 2 (fluid, circuit 2) |
| `MUX_CH_PUMP_3` | 4 | mp-Lowdriver ‚Äî Pump 3 (bubble removal, circuit 1) |
| `MUX_CH_PUMP_4` | 5 | mp-Lowdriver ‚Äî Pump 4 (bubble removal, circuit 2) |
| `MUX_CH_FLOW_1` | 6 | SLF3S-0600F ‚Äî Flow sensor 1 (circuit 1) |
| `MUX_CH_FLOW_2` | 7 | SLF3S-0600F ‚Äî Flow sensor 2 (circuit 2) |
